Summary of My Participation – Discussion Post 2

In my second discussion post, I explored the benefits and risks associated with the use of AI writers and automated writing systems across different contexts, including administrative tasks, professional communication, and creative writing. Based on Hutson’s (2021) article in Nature, I discussed how AI writing tools can improve productivity, support content generation, and assist users in completing writing tasks more efficiently.

I also critically examined the potential challenges associated with AI-generated content, including concerns related to accuracy, originality, intellectual property, ethical responsibility, and the potential impact on human creativity and professional roles. By reviewing relevant academic literature, I evaluated how machine learning technologies require careful implementation and governance to ensure responsible use.

This discussion enhanced my understanding of the practical applications of machine learning techniques and the importance of considering technical risks and uncertainties when deploying AI systems in real-world environments. It also developed my ability to critically analyse emerging AI technologies from both technological and ethical perspectives.
